## Less time for statistical modelling. The basic concepts (resulting objects, lists) are very important, but the rest (different estimation models) is usually very specific to the research question - everyone will have to look up / google for himself which functions and packages suit his needs best. Instead spend a little more time on data wrangling (frequently used functions for cleaning data).
